The paper focuses on deep learning and convolutional neural networks in the context of computer vision, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of labeled datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed method of guided labeling also involves decision-making and optimization, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing, which could place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, which could place it in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
